@aaronjensen I would not mind an all-javascript solution. Other than that, what are your thoughts so far?
#flowtype thoughts: I've tried different strategies for typing redux(-thunk) actions and they all are kinda crap
#flowtype thoughts: In retrospect, I might have opted for babel-register rather than a static file build for node-hosted flow app.
#flowtype thoughts: big thanks to @aaronjensen for the early help. Probably would have given up without it.
#flowtype thoughts: flow-typed definitions are a mixed bag. Good idea but confusing to work with.
#flowtype thoughts: tooling is important and much of it is very early days. Tried VS Code but ended up back in vim.
#flowtype thoughts: The body of online documentation and discussion ranges from confusing to outdated to useful (expected of new tech, TBH).
#flowtype thoughts: there is some friction to strictly segregating interfaces in javascript. Adding a type system can really help with that.
#flowtype thoughts: It has been really useful to me in places with many in-process transformations. Less so at process seams.
